docs.lead_paragraph: DIOCESE OF NEW-JERSEY.--On Palm Sunday, March 20, in St. Mary's Church, Burlington, Rev. Professor DOANE read morning prayer, and the Bishop preached, and confirmed twenty-two per sons, making forty-three in this parish since the last Convention.

docs.lead_paragraph: FROM LIBERIA.--Letters have been received from Rev. Bishop SCOTT, who left Baltimore last Fall, to visit the Methodist Missions in Liberia. The Bishop arrived at Monrovia on the 6th of Jan. in good health, which continued up to the 12th of that month, when the Bishop was about to leave Monrovia for Cape Palmas ; and he would probably be absent one month on that tour.

headline.main: Treatment of Strangers in Cuba--Letter from Mr. Skinner.

docs.lead_paragraph: The U. S. Mail steamship Crescent City, from New-Orleans and Havana, arrived yesterday morning, in four days and sixteen hours from Havana. The officers of the steamer report that there were a large number of European vessels in the harbor of Havana, awaiting cargoes.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Code was reported this morning, and a warm debate ensued on a motion to postpone the matter indefinitely. The ground taken in support of this motion was, that there was not time properly to consider the report during the present session. Some make this objection in good faith, others because they don't want the Code passed, and others still, because they want to ensure an extra sessession; but there will be no extra session.

headline.main: FROM HAVANA.; ARRIVAL OF THE CRESCENT CITY.

docs.lead_paragraph: The U. S. Mail steamship Crescent City, Capt. RODNEY BAXTER, arrived yesterday morning from New-Orleans and Havana, having left the latter port on the 10th inst. She brings three days later news, but there is little of importance.

docs.lead_paragraph: MISSING.--CHARLES E. DAVIS, Esq., Deputy Clerk of the Supreme Court, , in this city, suddenly disappeared last Friday morning, and has not since been heard of by his friends. Fears are entertained for his safety.
